Package org.apache.spark.network.shuffle

Interface BlockPushingListener

All Superinterfaces:
BlockTransferListener, EventListener
public interface BlockPushingListener extends BlockTransferListener
Callback to handle block push success and failure. This interface and BlockFetchingListener are unified under BlockTransferListener to allow code reuse for handling block push and fetch retry.

  • Method Details

    • onBlockPushSuccess

      void onBlockPushSuccess(String blockId, org.apache.spark.network.buffer.ManagedBuffer data)
      Called once per successfully pushed block. After this call returns, data will be released automatically. If the data will be passed to another thread, the receiver should retain() and release() the buffer on their own, or copy the data to a new buffer.
